name: Build your private blockchain on GCP

venue.name: Impact Hub Hong Kong
venue.address_1: 2/F International Industrial Building, 501-503 Castle Peak, Lai Chi Kok

group.name: Hong Kong Google Cloud Platform User Group (GCPUG.HK)

description:
This time we invited blockchain developer from RedSo to show us how to setup a private blockchain system (Hyperledger Fabric) on GCP.

Please follow https://facebook.com/groups/gcpughk for updates.

name: Build your Donkey Car with TensorFlow + Google Cloud Next Extended

venue.name: HK CoCoon
venue.address_1: 3/f, Citicorp Centre, 18 Whitfield Road, Causeway Bay

group.name: Hong Kong Google Cloud Platform User Group (GCPUG.HK)

description:
Google Cloud Next 18 has more than 100 new announcements. We are picking some important ones and sharing the experience of visiting the show.

We also invited Dennis and Jonathan from the Hong Kong Society of Autonomous Model Vehicles to share about how to build the AI driven DonkeyCar. Of course, we will have codes, and tracks for the car to run. You will see the live demo of the self driving car!

PS: drinks and light snacks will be included.

name: Hacking Saturday - DialogFlow Basics + Codelab

group.name: Hong Kong Google Cloud Platform User Group (GCPUG.HK)

description:
This event is co-organized with the Hong Kong Linux User Group.
Special thanks to Eaton Workshop sponsoring the super comfy space.

DialogFlow is a conversation engine for modern chatbot, offered by the Google Cloud Platform.
Edwin will briefly introduce the product and go through some codelabs together, so, please BRING YOUR LAPTOP to join the event.
After the session, you can stay at the venue till 6PM to continue the labs or social around!

*Limited snacks and drinks will be provided.
